  "title": "A Teen Was Stalked by a Great White — She Had No Idea",
  "script": "She was hunting a shark! Kayla Ross, a teenager visiting Santa Barbara from Colorado, heard a great white had been spotted offshore. So she and her uncle rented a paddleboard and paddled out — specifically to find it. They reviewed the drone footage when they got back. The shark had been right under her board the entire time. A 10-foot great white. Following her. For several minutes. Silent. Never broke the surface. Kayla had no idea until she was safely on shore, watching herself on a phone screen. She says she'd do it again. So the shark found the hunter — and just... watched. Should you tell Kayla she wasn't the one doing the hunting?",
